parameters.name: attributes
parameters.description: Represents a filtering mechanism where the elements within each inner array are logically ORed, and the resulting arrays are ANDed together at the top level. Each inner array consists of objects with two properties: traitType (a string) and value (a string). For example: [[{"traitType":"trait1", "value":"value1"},{"traitType":"trait1", "value":"value2"}]] would return listings that have "value1" OR "value2" for "trait1".

parameters.description: True to return aggregated marketplace listings, false to return just Magic Eden listings.

parameters.description: The direction returned elements should be sorted in, default 'asc'

parameters.name: paymentMints
parameters.description: Filter listings by the payment mint address that the seller expects. Default to filter for listings that only accept native SOL. Use "ALL" to show all listings.

get.summary: Get AMM pools corresponding to an owner or collection symbol. At least one of required collectionSymbol or owner is required!

allOf.description: Construct a type with the properties of T except for those in type K.

parameters.name: collectionSymbol
parameters.description: The collection symbol to query the pools from. At least this or "owner" must be passed in

parameters.name: pools
parameters.description: The pools key to query by.

parameters.name: owner
parameters.description: The owner public key to query the pools created by. At least this or "collectionSymbol" must be passed in

parameters.name: offset
parameters.description: The number of items to skip, default 0, min 0

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: The numbers of items to return, default 100, min 1, max 500

parameters.name: field
parameters.description: Sort pools by field. 0: NONE (no sorting field, default), 1: ADDRESS (sort pools by pool address), 2: SPOT_PRICE (sort pools by pool spot price), 5: BUYSIDE_ADJUSTED_PRICE (sort pools by buyside_adjusted_price = spot_price - royalty_fee - lp_fee)

parameters.name: direction
parameters.description: Sort pools by field in specified directions. 0: NONE (no sorting direction, default to increasing order if field is specified), 1: DESC (descending), 2: INC (increasing)
